<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="432" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[177,1084,1450,1560]" pageId="5" pageNumber="432">
C o m m e n t: This subgenus was previously represented in 
<collectingCountry box="[828,901,1450,1472]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="432">Turkey</collectingCountry>
by only one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(AUBE 1850)" baseAuthorityName="AUBE" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[234,517,1479,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuliginosa">
<emphasis box="[234,367,1479,1501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="432">L. fuliginosa</emphasis>
(AUBÉ 1850)
</taxonomicName>
, whose distribution is confined to the north; another species, 
<taxonomicName authority="COIFFAIT 1970" authorityName="COIFFAIT" authorityYear="1970" box="[263,523,1509,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerrutii">
<emphasis box="[263,366,1510,1531]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="432">L. cerrutii</emphasis>
COIFFAIT 1970
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to - and quite common in - 
<collectingCountry box="[920,993,1509,1531]" name="Cyprus" pageId="5" pageNumber="432">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
(ASSING &amp; WUNDERLE 2001) (
<figureCitation box="[399,467,1538,1560]" captionStart="Map 5" captionStartId="6.[177,222,770,791]" captionTargetBox="[177,1084,212,747]" captionTargetId="figure-2@6.[177,1084,212,747]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Map 5: Distribution of the subgenus Dysleptusa PACE in Turkey and Cyprus: L. fuliginosa (AUBÉ) (filled circles), L. improvisa nov.sp. (filled square), and L. cerrutii COIFFAIT (open circles)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276181/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="432">Map 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
